##Late at night on the streets of Wuhan, he rode a battery car to deliver medicine

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

ABSTRACT: Starting from January 23,2020, Wu Yu, with the idea of "should do something" , turned into a "rider" and rode his little electric bicycle to the streets of Wuhan, delivering face masks, alcohol and drugs to the families of the patients who were in need. Currently, he and his students deliver medicine to 250 families. Plus the ones we sent before, we're up to 500 now.

By Nancy Cheung

Editor | 林鹏

Wu You of Wuhan, the Vlog, the most frequent is the night of empty streets, dark roads, his battery car hit a mass of bright yellow lights printed on the ground, accompanied by his bloated shadow. The car drives forward, the Lens Shakes, Wu Yo soliloquizes where to deliver medicine again today, the exhausted voice accompanies the sound of the wind.

Battery car is black and white, the front of the car with colored dots of Windproof cotton-padded Jacket, there is a small basket under the lights, usually filled with supplies, the basket empty, that day's task completed. Wu removed his steamy yellow-rimmed goggles, leaving two parallel imprints on his forehead and eyes.

Wu You, 26, is a native of Wuhan. Before the COVID-19 epidemic spread, he was an intern teacher in a middle school in Wuhan and a part time teacher in a counseling organization. He has a wide range of hobbies. He studied abroad to learn recording engineering, make movies, music videos, and usually engage in rap.

From January 23,2020, Wu Yu, with the idea of "should do something, " turned into a "horseman" and rode his little electric bicycle around the streets of Wuhan, delivering face masks, alcohol and drugs to the families of patients who were in need.

The patient with fever gets medicine, had a few days buffer period, go to community register, wait for bed to be hospitalized, insist again come down.

Most of the time, he didn't dare to stay long, and many of the people asking for help could only see the top of his head through the peephole of the security door. Sometimes they even talked back to back. Wu said, the important thing is that the drug can be sent to each other's hands, he is not a hero, also afraid of infection.

Wuhan became haggard, but for the first time in more than twenty years he really looked at the city. When he was driving through the empty Shouyi Square after delivering medicine, he stopped for a while and suddenly realized the spirit of Wuhan People, as long as he thought it was right, he first made it and then said it.

Here's what he said:

"You can't wear a mask alone. You have to wear both. "

I am Wuhan Hong Kong road a training organization's teacher, also in a middle school internship, as a teacher, the students are 00. When the outbreak spread, the students were so scared, I didn't know how to comfort them.

My grandfather used to be in charge of sanitation in the army. At home, he was watching the news on TV and said, "it's no use to wear a mask alone, only if you wear it. " I kept thinking about what my grandfather said. He didn't like staying at home and didn't want to be an outsider, i wanted to tell my students that I wasn't a superhero, but I could solve some problems, so I started giving away some masks I had saved at home.

On the first day of the New Year, I went out with 300 masks, a pack of 50, and Rode my bike down the road. It was a cloudy day. The street was empty. It didn't go out. Later, I went to the neighborhood committee, word spread quickly, sent only 100, and to the next neighborhood, less than two hours to light up.

A lot of people thought I was a government worker, and asked me how long I'd been shut down, and I said, I'm not from the government, so why do you hand out masks? I said I was a volunteer, and they didn't get it.

A few days later, my student joined, he rode a bicycle, I drove a battery car, we wrote a sign "free to help deliver mask, medicine. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wu Yau / tumblr

I remember the first person who asked for help, she had a fever, and there was nothing near her house, and she asked me to bring her some tylenol. I went to the drug store to buy Amoxicillin and CEPHALOSPORINS, and rode the 8 km to the rendezvous, dropped off the pills, turned around, watched his boyfriend come out to get them, yelled thank you across the street, and left me a pack of cigarettes.

When the city was sealed off, supplies were tight. One morning, we ran all the pharmacies within 5 kilometers, only to find a box of Lianhua qingwen capsules, or a grass-prefixed pirated ("Lotus" Qingwen) . One time, we had to take apart a board of capsules, half from this family, half from that family. Prices in Arbidol have tripled. Masks are a dime a dozen and the price of rubbing alcohol has doubled. (editor's Note: On February 4, Chinese Academy of Engineering, a member of the high level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, and her team announced the latest research results on the treatment of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan. They found that Arbidol could significantly inhibit coronavirus replication and recommended that it be included in the sixth edition of the COVID-19.)

At first it was just me and the students, but as more people joined, our division of Labor became clearer: Online volunteers registered their drug needs, friends helped send in supplies from out of town, and we planned our route in advance and sent them to the people who needed help.

Now we have a group that delivers drugs to 250 families. Plus the ones we sent before, we're up to 500 now.

Most of the delivery is to reduce the fever of Oseltamivir, a box tube a day, the adult version is not, we all eat children's version, so the consumption of large. Now Wuhan people already have a tacit understanding, like Arbidol, these drugs are very difficult to buy, people will not ask.

We designed the route for the next day based on the information we requested the night before, and sometimes it took us a long time to get to two hundred meters. The route had better be a circle. The larger the area, the better.

I deliver medicine to one family for four days at a time, leaving at 11 a.m. , and returning, sometimes until 1 or 2 in the morning. My battery car runs on one battery for two hours, about 50 kilometers. This small electric car was used to buy food, distraction, and now run nearly 1000 kilometers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Charging on the ride / photo by interviewee

To save space, I unpacked the box, took a big bag of pills, and went straight to the office: A 4 board Combo, 50 bags of Oseltamivir, plus 380 ml of alcohol, 20 face masks, like some kind of package deal.

One of the headaches is finding new sources of medicine every three or four days, one after the other, clearing the air, Oseltamivir, Moxifloxacin. Find One, take a breath, find the next. First my friend's drug company, now he's got three or four connections.

When the first batch of medicine arrived, I was quite happy, so I went out with a whole box, the battery car had no place to put its feet, five or six plastic bags were hung on the front of the car, alcohol was stuffed in my schoolbag, and I was bloated like a Michelin man with tires.

But the problem is, when I get to my destination, I can't just leave it there in case I lose it. So I had to go upstairs with a big box of medicine, and some of the patients thought I was gonNA give it to them, but it only lasted three days in a box, and it had side effects, so I didn't send much out.

In addition to the mainstream of a few drugs, but also to treat breast cancer, hypertension, heart disease and so on, so pull a docking of non-new Coronary Disease Drug Group.

At first I was free drug delivery, now part of the drug store prices, free masks and alcohol. On the one hand, the economic pressure, the cushion more than 10,000, the other is to prevent the "Extension Party" , or someone hoarding medicine. Some people said before that a mask did not, let me send, someone sent my wechat directly to all kinds of family groups, colleagues, all come to ask for medicine, this goes against our original intention of giving emergency treatment to patients, the principle is that patients, the elderly and young first.

The security door only sees the top of my head through the peephole

My gear is usually a motorcycle helmet, a jacket with a chin, and leather gloves to wipe off the alcohol. Now they wear protective clothing, goggles, gloves. Gloves changed every day, but protective clothing, glasses material tension, come back after disinfection, hanging outside ventilation.

It's a little scary at first, thinking about the scene in the movie contagion and not being able to communicate with each other, sometimes I'd knock on the door and then I'd leave, and the most they could see was the top of my head in the peephole of the security door, sometimes to save time, drop it like a bowling ball on the stairs, call it in.

Special period we speak very clean and tidy, are directly asked "XX drugs have it? " , No nonsense.

Once the person who asked for help came out to get medicine, wearing a yellow nightgown, like a joint in infernal affairs, when he appeared was a back, leaning against the railing, he said, is that you? And I said, "yeah, I put it there for you. ".

Sometimes to send medicine to the elderly, the elderly can not explain the place, to the destination will linger there for a long time, take half an hour to find the place. Some old people do not know who I am, and I forget the name of the person asking for help, I said to the old people in general, "your relatives called me to give you" , the old people asked how much money, I said, your relatives have given.

Just put it in the hands of people, try not to touch it, but there are accidents.

On January 27th, I was delivering medicine to a patient who had been diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia. He came up to me and bowed. I threw my disposable raincoat in the trash. I poured 84 bottles of disinfectant to keep the sanitation workers from getting infected, take off your coat, shine it on the hot air, and take a hot bath.

There were news reports that patients on the 8th floor never made it to the 7th floor, but the 7th floor was infected, and hearing these extreme cases, you think, what if you're next?

On January 30th, he was delivering medicine to a suspected patient, he came up with the medicine, I was on the right side of the scooter, he was on the left side, he wanted to transfer the money to me, I said it was okay, he probably didn't hear me either, just leaned his head over and said something, i'll just pretend to answer the phone and go.

When I got home, I immediately took the medicine. I had a heart operation, and MOXIFLOXACIN had side effects on his heart. He took it that day.

But then I got over it, and I lost one, and I saved at least two, so that's more money. Later I heard that the delivery of those days is very critical, a few days to take medicine so that they have a buffer period, contact the hospital.

Up to now, my mother still do not know what I am doing, a few days ago I was on satellite TV, but just she went to buy food, did not see.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wu You's Vlog / tumblr

My Dad knows what I'm doing. He once sent me a message of encouragement, saying how proud he was of me. In fact, both of us are not very good at expressing feelings, he has never sent me such a long message six or seven rows.

Occasionally very big pressure, will think of the front-line doctors, they may still be younger than me, so big pressure, I can not but carry pressure.

One family impressed me very much. An old couple in their 80s contracted new coronary pneumonia. Their son and daughter-in-law in their 50s went to take care of them. They were infected. A young man in his 20s went to take care of his parents again. They were infected again. They infected their daughter-in-law, six members of the family, top to bottom, all but the children.

They lived in the neighborhood across from me, and my granddaughter, who was in the least of her problems, came to me for help. I saw her circle of friends, and I was worried. Now the whole family is in different hospitals, the old man is very serious, used the breathing machine.

Theoretically speaking, they were infected before the "closure" of the city. At that time, the message was "limited human-to-human transmission. " They also did not attract attention. At first, they thought it was the flu and did not know how to protect themselves.

My area of operation is in Hankou, but people often ask, when will Wuchang and Aoyama Come? Sometimes it's so far, it's 60 kilometers each way, but I still go. Always said the next day to rest, the next day and out of the students.

Sometimes a breakdown is psychological. There was a mother who asked for help. She wasn't diagnosed, but she was desperate. Her husband was gone, and she would always say that if she lost herself, the children would follow. In case something happened to her, I gave her my number, told her to call me if she needed anything, and kept it on 24 hours a day.

There were some very warm moments. One day I delivered medicine to my home near two o'clock in the evening. 30 kilometers away from home, my cell phone and battery car were out of power. I said a word in the group. My friends and patients immediately started to act. One person rode a bicycle to deliver the charging treasure, and another person walked to deliver the charging wire, i push the car two or three kilometers, another family to help me lift the car upstairs to charge, that day home is already five in the morning, but the heart is very moved.

The spirit of Wuhan people, "do it and then say it. "

Before my grandmother brain hemorrhage, is still conscious, CT scan showed no new pneumonia, my father wanted to take her to the hospital, but ran several hospitals have no beds. On Feb. 9, I posted a message asking for your opinion, and the next day I saw at least 100 private messages, which I eventually retweeted to nearly 20,000.

Concorde, Tongji Hospital professor to see the situation, called to see the grandmother's CT, said can rest at home, later sent grandma to the central hospital injection, the situation is stable.

I've been helped, and I'm helping people. Now many people also want to join us, we choose people will be more cautious, try to choose the city concerned about the local people, and then the body can bear, can not three days fishing two days. Some time ago I heard that a volunteer picked up a car's supplies. I don't know where it went. It was all supplies to the hospital. Other volunteers called the police.

I am 90, usually I am quite a personality, in the training class teaching media, in a middle school is an internship teacher, studied abroad to learn recording engineering, shoot MV, engaged in e-sports. But when it comes to commonality, there is also a great deal of empathy.

Wuhan used to have a rich night life. Now it's dark at night. At six or seven o'clock, there's nothing. My place is very close to the riverbank. Now it's closed. I don't even want to buy a glove or borrow a charger, how many roads does it take to get to a lonely convenience store.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo by Ng Yau in class / interviewee

Previously said that "the present life is not easy, you have to cherish" , are very perfunctory to say, now feel, that is really not the general hard-won. This place is getting gaunt, but I love it even more. On one occasion, I came back from delivering medicine. I passed the Shouyi Square commemorating the 1911 Revolution. It used to be crowded with traffic. Now it is bare and empty.

I stood there for a while and looked up the history of the 1911 Revolution on my mobile phone because the news leaked and a revolution was set off ahead of time in Wuhan. Yi Zhongtian's evaluation of the Wuhan people is the spirit of "make and then say" , before no feelings, but now I and students, friends around, in doing these things, as long as they think right, make and then say, "What if it's 60 kilometers away and you can't go back? ".

This time a lot of media have come to interview me, at first I wanted to be a little bit more official, like a textbook, under the national flag to speak that kind of feeling. But in fact, my heart is very simple, four words, "fuck to say" . At first I thought it would be over by the end of the day, but now I've been doing it for so long, I think it's the right thing to do.

Before the outbreak, I had a script that I was working on with my best friend to see at a small film festival in the United States. The tickets are canceled. The festival's canceled. My friend in Wuhan was in the United States, the United States has influenza B, Wuhan has a new coronary pneumonia, he was in a dilemma, later went to Shenzhen.

After the outbreak ended, most want to go out for a trip. Before this matter, I thought I was a pretty ordinary person, but a bit more hobby, now I feel some changes, more burden, not familiar with the people would think I was indifferent, this time also re-know me.
